title: Encrypt a tflite file in C++
body:
I am trying to use a custom tflite model on browser. A simple C++ file reads the model and interprets it. This C++ file is converted to WebAssembly to be able to run on browser. The tflite model is basically a FlatBuffer file, Want to know how can I encrypt it. I am looking for a fast encryption/decryption method implemented on C++.

I would implement the decryption code with the key on the C++ file, And as it would be converted to WebAssembly, No one would be able to access the original C++ file and get the key.
